---
description: Protect Bunny Storage and media flow
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Media and asset rules:
- preserve existing Bunny Storage usage if present
- do not replace media flow with another storage provider
- do not hardcode storage secrets
- do not fake upload success
- do not change URL/path assumptions unless required for a bug fix
- do not alter media rendering behavior unless explicitly requested
- do not introduce a new CDN or storage service unless explicitly requested

Allowed:
- improve upload error handling
- improve retry logic
- improve typing
- improve performance
- fix broken media paths with minimal diff

Default behavior:
preserve existing media flow and storage assumptions.
